title: New Mexico High School Volleyball Rankings
text:
New Mexico High School Volleyball Rankings Joshua J. Grine NMPreps.com Basketball Analyst 
Each Monday on NMPreps.com we rank the Top 25 teams in New Mexico Volleyball Teams regardless of Class. 
The Onate Lady Knights are 10-5 and 3-0 in district play this season NMPreps.com Top 25 Volleyball Rankings 
1. La Cueva (14-0, 4-0) 2. St. Pius X (11-2, 1-0) 3. Sandia Prep (13-0, 2-0) 4. Centennial (12-2, 3-1) 6. Volcano Vista (10-4, 4-0) 7. Los Lunas (10-3, 4-0) 8. Texico (12-1, 0-0) - Moved +2 9. Roswell (12-2, 0-0) - Moved +2 10. Cleveland (7-8, 2-1) - Moved +2 See The Top 25 Here Week 8: Onate The Threat in 6A, Others Playing Musical Chairs 
Week eight was a quiet one across the state of New Mexico with many schools going on fall break. Not many games but some played a significant roll in the rankings. 
More teams started their district schedule, while a few others played outside their district schedule and others are making the trend up in their district placement. The bubble is alive and well in many classifications and we take a look at many of the headlines.... Continue Reading Here THE BIG FOUR FROM WEEK 8 
3A Volleyball: No. 8 Texico over Melrose, 3-0. The darlings of the state of New Mexico, No. 8 Texico Lady Wolverines (12-1, 0-0) are continuing their magical season with a convincing.... Continue Reading Here 
4A Volleyball: Portales over Artesia, 3-2. The minor upset last week is likely this contest as the Portales Rams (4-8, 0-0) who have had a bit of a disappointing campaign had a big win over then top-25 ranked Artesia (10-4, 0-0), 3-2. .... Continue Reading Here 
5A Volleyball: No. 21 Piedra Vista over Miyamura, 3-0. Maybe, not the headline for "Big Four, but the No. 21 Piedra Vista Lady Panthers (11-4, 4-0) having been quietly moving in and up the rankings. This team has been consistently in the top of the class and should have a little more respect than they have been given this season. .... Continue Reading Here 
6A Volleyball: No. 15 Sandia over No. 11 Eldorado, 3-1. Now to the "upset" of the week is the Sandia Matadors.... Continue Reading Here Top 50 Performers 
A Medina (Atrisco Heritage/2017) - 9 kills in loss to West Mesa. Aisha Ruiz (Atrisco Heritage/2018) - 6 kills, 1 block in loss to West Mesa. Faith Gorman (Atrisco Heritage/2017) - 20 digs, 17 assists in loss to West Mesa. Marisa Chavez (Atrisco Heritage/2016) - 24 digs in loss to West Mesa. Bianca Castro (Gadsden/2017) - 5 blocks in loss to Mayfield.
